01:45:22.721 --> 01:45:28.775
from the blast of the fireball, the wood itself
darkened and splintered in places. You can see

01:45:28.775 --> 01:45:36.659
that giant, burned U that marks the deck.
Everything is held in place. You're making your

01:45:36.659 --> 01:45:42.299
way to the guards. What are you doing, Jester? You
see Beau being led up by the guards towards the

01:45:42.299 --> 01:45:43.715
Throne Roost.

01:45:43.715 --> 01:45:51.812
LAURA: Okay, you can do it, Beau. Do I see the big
fire explosion too, as it happens?

01:45:51.812 --> 01:45:56.369
MATT: Oh yeah, you saw and heard the distant
(explosion).

01:45:56.369 --> 01:45:57.382
TALIESIN: Whitestone saw the fire.

01:45:57.382 --> 01:46:00.152
TRAVIS: (singing) Whitestone saw the fire.

01:46:00.152 --> 01:46:08.951
LAURA: Oh. Okay. I hope everyone's okay. Please,
Traveler, be with them. I'm going to start running

01:46:08.951 --> 01:46:12.939
towards the docks in disguise.

01:46:12.939 --> 01:46:19.263
MATT: Okay. The guards have now pulled you all to
your feet, and have begun to apply manacles to

01:46:19.263 --> 01:46:27.390
your hands. Not anything too aggressive, but for
the purpose of safety and to maintain the order

01:46:27.390 --> 01:46:35.121
within this community, they're particular and
careful. They also go onto the deck, and you see

01:46:35.121 --> 01:46:43.773
them beginning to collect the bodies of those that
were killed. Bouldergut is inconsolable and

01:46:43.773 --> 01:46:51.845
furious, and it takes a few guards to get her to
calm down. Avantika is having a conversation with

01:46:51.845 --> 01:47:00.602
a couple of the guards. You guys are being pulled
away from the docks, towards the city. As you are

01:47:00.602 --> 01:47:07.185
brought towards the edge of it, one of the guards,
adorned a little better than the rest, have a

01:47:07.185 --> 01:47:15.768
brief discussion. You overhear one of them say,
"Hold tight, apparently someone's going to get the

01:47:15.792 --> 01:47:24.018
"Plank King." While you guys are all waiting, and
you're going to convene with the rest of your troupe--

01:47:24.018 --> 01:47:26.255
LAURA: I'm not going to join them.

01:47:26.255 --> 01:47:27.808
MATT: But go and find the vicinity.

01:47:27.808 --> 01:47:28.897
LAURA: See what's going on, yeah.

01:47:28.897 --> 01:47:34.211
MATT: There are many looky-loos on the edges of
the shipyards here. The docks make up probably a

01:47:34.211 --> 01:47:40.482
good third of Darktow. Before you actually get the
edge of the cliff where the city itself is built

01:47:40.482 --> 01:47:45.950
on different areas and platforms, and the streets
all rise at a perpetual grade, as it is embedded

01:47:45.950 --> 01:47:51.345
in the side of the cliff. There are folks who are
looking over to see what happened. Usually this

01:47:51.345 --> 01:47:56.432
kind of stuff does not go down within the city.
You can see that people are excited, and worried,

01:47:56.432 --> 01:48:00.358
and making up their own stories, and what they
saw. One of them is like, "It was crazy! A demon

01:48:00.358 --> 01:48:06.951
"fell from the sky and slammed into the boat and it
was intense!" The rumors are going crazy.

01:48:06.951 --> 01:48:08.687
MARISHA: It was a Gwar concert.

01:48:08.687 --> 01:48:13.206
MATT: That's a 7th-level spell, Summon Gwar
Concert.

01:48:13.206 --> 01:48:18.031
LAURA: (old man voice) Did Avantika finally do it?
Did she finally do it?

01:48:18.031 --> 01:48:19.229
SAM: She's still trying?

01:48:19.229 --> 01:48:22.247
LAURA: I always heard that she was going to stage
a coup. Did she finally stage one?

01:48:22.247 --> 01:48:25.577
(laughter)

01:48:25.577 --> 01:48:31.128
TALIESIN: If I can take ten minutes of this time
sitting manacled to cast Prayer-- if enough of us

01:48:31.128 --> 01:48:32.769
are within 30 feet of each other right now.

01:48:32.769 --> 01:48:37.629
MATT: You can probably all-- they do round you up.
However, as soon as you begin to make any physical

01:48:37.629 --> 01:48:39.166
action towards spellcasting--

01:48:39.166 --> 01:48:40.137
TALIESIN: It's all vocal.

01:48:40.137 --> 01:48:41.089
MATT: It's only verbal?

01:48:41.089 --> 01:48:44.277
TALIESIN: It's only verbal. And I tell them.

01:48:44.277 --> 01:48:46.683
MATT: You tell them you're going to cast a spell?

01:48:46.683 --> 01:48:49.759
TALIESIN: I'm going to be healing everybody. It's
a thing that I--

01:48:49.759 --> 01:48:51.257
MATT: "No spellcasting."

01:48:51.257 --> 01:48:53.649
TALIESIN: (loud sigh)

01:48:53.649 --> 01:48:55.570
MATT: "Don't want any funny stuff."

01:48:55.570 --> 01:48:57.561
TALIESIN: All right, that's fine.

01:48:57.561 --> 01:48:58.870
SAM: Have they taken our weapons?

01:48:58.870 --> 01:49:04.017
MATT: They have, after manacling, taken your
weapons. The individuals are carrying them at

01:49:04.017 --> 01:49:06.235
their side. Not yours. They couldn't find yours.

01:49:06.235 --> 01:49:08.041
TRAVIS: I wonder why.

01:49:08.041 --> 01:49:16.504
MATT: They have your crossbow, and they've taken
your shield and your staff.

01:49:16.504 --> 01:49:22.377
LAURA: Am I within range of everybody? Could I be
in the crowd, but near everyone?

01:49:22.499 --> 01:49:28.512
(laughter)

01:49:28.512 --> 01:49:32.969
MATT: There is a small perimeter being held, but
you could get probably within 20, 25 feet or so of them.

01:49:32.969 --> 01:49:37.549
LAURA: Then, if I'm within 30 feet, I'm going to
cast Prayer of Healing on my buds.

01:49:37.549 --> 01:49:38.777
MATT: Okay.

01:49:38.777 --> 01:49:41.259
MARISHA: What? On your buds?

01:49:41.259 --> 01:49:42.485
LAURA: On my buddies!

01:49:42.485 --> 01:49:49.506
MATT: Make a performance check to see how subtly
you can-- no, this would be deception. Make a deception.

01:49:49.506 --> 01:49:51.173
LAURA: A deception check. Okay.

01:49:51.173 --> 01:49:52.581
TRAVIS: Come on.

01:49:52.581 --> 01:49:59.910
LAURA: Eight. Well, I hope those people are going to be
okay. They look like they're pretty hurt up in

01:49:59.968 --> 01:50:04.561
there. Some of them look like they're bloody. That
one looks burned.

01:50:04.561 --> 01:50:07.992
MATT: As you begin to subtly try and sneak your
verbal components of your spell into the

01:50:07.992 --> 01:50:13.987
discussion, one of the guards goes: "Hey! Sorry,
we're making sure there's no casting this close to

01:50:13.987 --> 01:50:16.838
"it, if you don't mind."

01:50:16.838 --> 01:50:21.192
LAURA: Makes sense. I just saw some were hurt. I
was trying to help out, but if they don't want it,

01:50:21.192 --> 01:50:22.709
then I ain't going to do it.

01:50:22.709 --> 01:50:25.890
MATT: "It's best not to get involved. Terribly
sorry about that."

01:50:25.890 --> 01:50:28.384
SAM: I want to hear more!

01:50:28.384 --> 01:50:30.019
MATT: Nah, that's it.

01:50:30.019 --> 01:50:32.989
LIAM: No! It was so good!

01:50:32.989 --> 01:50:35.096
TALIESIN: This is what you get for Counterspell.

01:50:35.096 --> 01:50:41.764
MATT: He's telling everyone, "Please, hold tight.
Don't worry. We're taking care of it."

01:50:41.764 --> 01:50:47.614
TALIESIN: It's just a cheek caress, then gone. Not
even a kiss goodnight.

01:50:47.614 --> 01:50:54.554
MATT: Anyway, about 30 or so minutes pass for the
rest of you. As make your way up the steps now,

01:50:54.554 --> 01:51:01.894
trying to jaunt, you manage to catch up to the
armored fellow, who now acts as the tip of the

01:51:01.894 --> 01:51:06.719
spear, essentially. Now you're flanked and to the
front, although the flanking has to shift as the

01:51:06.719 --> 01:51:12.021
space for the steps ascending to the Throne Roost
get only wide for one person at a time. You are

01:51:12.021 --> 01:51:19.868
being held at that point. You make your way up to
the Throne Roost, to the shelf of stone. There you

01:51:19.940 --> 01:51:26.147
see, standing at the edge, is the Plank King
himself, blackened curls still dangling around his

01:51:26.235 --> 01:51:32.092
massive goliath head, his long coat billowing
slightly with the bit of wind that's whipping

01:51:32.092 --> 01:51:41.751
around the side of the cliff face. The morning fog
is burning off of the nearby reefs, and you can

01:51:41.751 --> 01:51:49.435
see a little bit further out. The sky itself is
still dull gray. Looks over and goes, "That was

01:51:49.435 --> 01:51:57.459
"quite the display, wouldn't you say?" The guard
goes, "Right, sir. One of them, we found at least

01:51:57.459 --> 01:52:03.196
"someone running from the bit who says they have
information for you." He goes, "Oh yeah, no, I

01:52:03.196 --> 01:52:05.700
"recognize this one. Step forward."

01:52:05.700 --> 01:52:07.568
MARISHA: 'Sup?

01:52:07.568 --> 01:52:11.452
MATT: "So what's all this?"

01:52:11.452 --> 01:52:16.588
MARISHA: What, the display you just saw, or this?

01:52:16.588 --> 01:52:19.895
MATT: "If you don't mind, tell me what's going
on."

01:52:19.895 --> 01:52:25.336
MARISHA: I think you just won the lottery, friend.
I toss him the book.

01:52:25.336 --> 01:52:32.475
MATT: He flips through the pages. "This is
gibberish."

01:52:32.475 --> 01:52:37.586
MARISHA: I know. Luckily, one of our crew members
is smart enough, and he deciphered the whole

01:52:37.586 --> 01:52:43.110
thing. In there you'll find everything you need to
know about the coup that Avantika has been

01:52:43.110 --> 01:52:52.802
planning. Whispers about wanting to rule the sea.
She has been worshipping an outer-worldly being

01:52:52.802 --> 01:52:57.037
called Uk'otoa, left over from the Betrayer Gods.

01:52:57.986 --> 01:53:03.390
MATT: He glances through the paperwork, looks at
you giving him this sly grin, and goes, "You,

01:53:03.390 --> 01:53:13.661
"newcomer into these waters, spent less than a day
amongst our people and have already attacked and

01:53:13.661 --> 01:53:15.511
"stolen from one of our own, as well."

01:53:15.511 --> 01:53:18.363
MARISHA: I didn't attack; she attacked us first.

01:53:18.363 --> 01:53:26.071
MATT: "Well, we'll see what she has to say to
defend herself, as well. Hang tight with me here,

01:53:26.071 --> 01:53:31.607
"with these men. The rest of you, get the rest of
your guard. Bring her friends, and bring Avantika

01:53:31.607 --> 01:53:35.558
"and who else had survived that massacre up here to
the roost."

01:53:35.558 --> 01:53:40.617
MARISHA: You're going to trust the things that she
says? You'll see a U burned into the deck of the ship.

01:53:40.617 --> 01:53:45.589
MATT: "I don't trust anyone, and I trust more
those that I've mistrusted for years than those

01:53:45.589 --> 01:53:54.224
"I've only come to mistrust and know right now. So
we'll see where it all lies. Be patient. If what

01:53:54.224 --> 01:53:57.890
"you say is true, then we've got all time in the
day."

01:53:57.890 --> 01:53:59.405
MARISHA: You have time to read that book right
now?

01:53:59.405 --> 01:54:03.694
MATT: "I don't read a fucking piece of this, but
I've got a few friends who are more of a

01:54:03.694 --> 01:54:06.019
"page-turning type."

01:54:06.019 --> 01:54:09.990
MARISHA: Hey, you came to me, though. Why?

01:54:09.990 --> 01:54:16.480
MATT: "Because I wanted to see if you'd actually
do something. Remember, we don't turn on pirates here."

01:54:16.480 --> 01:54:21.675
MARISHA: What do I get when I'm right?

01:54:21.675 --> 01:54:25.708
MATT: "If you're right, then I'll judge you based
on the fact that you broke our law as soon as you

01:54:25.708 --> 01:54:32.224
"got here, and I'll weigh it versus how positive
this tells me. There's not enough, well, maybe you

01:54:32.224 --> 01:54:36.220
"and Avantika will find yourselves out there on a
pike of warning."

01:54:36.220 --> 01:54:40.086
MARISHA: How about we strike a deal right now?
Because when you go down there, you're going to

01:54:40.086 --> 01:54:45.877
see murdered crew mates and a U burned into the
deck of that ship from where she was trying to

01:54:45.877 --> 01:54:49.484
summon Uk'otoa.

01:54:49.902 --> 01:54:52.604
MATT: Make a deception check.

01:54:52.604 --> 01:54:55.137
SAM and LAURA: Oh god.

01:54:55.137 --> 01:55:00.640
LIAM: (whispers) You crazy motherfucker.

01:55:01.405 --> 01:55:02.927
MARISHA: 17.

01:55:02.927 --> 01:55:07.620
MATT: Okay. He nods a bit.

01:55:07.620 --> 01:55:11.394
MARISHA: So if you think you can trust anything
that she says before you get into the details of

01:55:11.394 --> 01:55:17.040
that book, details that we've already deciphered,
as we've been on the seas with her for quite some

01:55:17.040 --> 01:55:21.210
time, and the betrayal that we have seen.

01:55:21.210 --> 01:55:26.036
MATT: "So's this one." He snaps his fingers, and
you see a cloaked figure step out of the shadows,

01:55:26.036 --> 01:55:29.025
the same cloak that passed you on the stairs the
night before.

01:55:29.025 --> 01:55:30.254
TRAVIS: Oh, right.

01:55:30.254 --> 01:55:31.349
LAURA: Is it Jamedi?

01:55:31.349 --> 01:55:33.495
MATT: It's Jamedi, hood pulled back.

01:55:33.495 --> 01:55:36.025
SAM: Is he with us?

01:55:36.025 --> 01:55:37.601
LAURA: I like Jamedi.

01:55:37.601 --> 01:55:39.234
TRAVIS: Jamedi does not like her.

01:55:39.234 --> 01:55:44.104
MATT: At which point, the Plank King steps up
towards you, now looming over you, a good two and

01:55:44.104 --> 01:55:50.883
a half feet of height on you. This imposing
presence, wide like a mountain, glancing down at

01:55:50.883 --> 01:55:55.689
you with a grin. You can smell his early morning
breath of rotting teeth and whatever he had the

01:55:55.689 --> 01:56:05.831
night before pulsing from his grin. He goes, "I
have to say, for someone so small, you've got some

01:56:05.831 --> 01:56:07.364
"serious balls."

01:56:09.099 --> 01:56:12.049
MARISHA: Thanks. That's not the first time I've
heard that.

01:56:12.049 --> 01:56:18.730
MATT: "And if you survive, I'm sure it won't be
the last. All right. Let's go see your friends."

01:56:18.730 --> 01:56:28.696
MARISHA: Hey! I want a boat, and safe passage out
if we're correct.

01:56:28.696 --> 01:56:36.509
MATT: "If this is right, let's hope you didn't
blow up too much of her boat; it'll be yours."

01:56:36.509 --> 01:56:39.156
MARISHA: Deal.

01:56:39.156 --> 01:56:43.032
MATT: "If it's enough."

01:56:43.032 --> 01:56:48.759
TRAVIS: Oh god. (choking)

01:56:48.759 --> 01:56:52.242
MATT: The guards now turn and spin you around and
push you back down the stairs as the Plank King

01:56:52.242 --> 01:56:58.823
follows behind, Jamedi keeping a close watch. He
goes and shouts something off to the side. He

01:56:58.823 --> 01:57:06.323
goes, "Solon! I'm going to need your brain for
this one. Come on." You hear a voice go, "All

01:57:06.323 --> 01:57:07.557
"right, I'm coming."

01:57:07.557 --> 01:57:09.958
LIAM and TRAVIS: Solon?

01:57:09.958 --> 01:57:18.850
MATT: Solon. S-O-L-O-N. Coming around the corner,
you see a human man, probably in his late 50s,

01:57:18.850 --> 01:57:28.448
early 60s. Bit of an unkept puff of a chin goatee,
his hair thinning in this big widow's peak, gray

01:57:28.448 --> 01:57:39.549
to white. These big spectacles around his eyes,
and this tattered, thin mustache that's attempted

01:57:39.549 --> 01:57:45.476
to be curled into a handlebar, but it seems to
have split in places and is not very well kept. He

01:57:45.476 --> 01:57:51.265
has this big, green cloak that's wrapped around
his shoulders that is so much material and

01:57:51.265 --> 01:57:56.621
billowing so widely, it makes his head
comparatively look much smaller. He's clutching a

01:57:56.621 --> 01:58:01.619
bag, and he's getting his stuff. "Wait here, I'm
getting my stuff. Ugh!" They keep walking, and

01:58:01.619 --> 01:58:06.516
eventually you see him trying to catch up from
behind. (panting) You take it this was probably

01:58:06.516 --> 01:58:09.857
what the Plank King was referring to as his
bookish friend.

01:58:09.857 --> 01:58:11.228
TRAVIS: You think?

01:58:11.228 --> 01:58:12.670
LIAM: Yeah.

01:58:12.670 --> 01:58:15.621
TRAVIS: He's the fighter.

01:58:17.635 --> 01:58:21.661
MATT: As you guys are all patiently waiting here,
looking amongst yourselves, is there anything you

01:58:21.661 --> 01:58:30.369
wish to do, or are you succumbing to the hope that
Jester, Beauregard, and/or possibly the Plank King

01:58:30.369 --> 01:58:34.934
comes to situate this? Eventually, you see
Avantika brought up from the ship in manacles, as well.

01:58:34.934 --> 01:58:39.306
LIAM: Well, I've noticed that they're not letting
any of us cast anything, correct?

01:58:39.306 --> 01:58:41.406
MATT: No, they shut that down.

01:58:41.406 --> 01:58:44.032
LIAM: Then no. I would do Mage Armor, but no.

01:58:44.032 --> 01:58:46.768
TALIESIN: This is basically a short rest? Is this
what this is?

01:58:46.768 --> 01:58:48.485
MATT: It's not quite long enough to be a short
rest.

01:58:48.485 --> 01:58:49.491
LIAM: Motherfucker.

01:58:49.491 --> 01:58:51.192
TRAVIS: I know, I was going to say the same
thing.

01:58:51.192 --> 01:58:54.861
MATT: Actually, you know what? No, it's about an
hour of short rest. I give that to you.

01:58:54.861 --> 01:58:55.909
TRAVIS: Bless you, Mercer.

01:58:55.909 --> 01:58:58.285
MATT: For the travel of Beau to the front, and the
rest of the guard to get there; for the Plank King

01:58:58.285 --> 01:59:01.040
conversation; for him to descend the Throne Roost
to make his way through the city to the docks;

01:59:01.040 --> 01:59:02.275
yeah, that's over an hour.

01:59:02.275 --> 01:59:07.529
LIAM: Then in these circumstances, I would dismiss
Frumpkin from the Material Plane and bring him

01:59:07.529 --> 01:59:10.364
back on my shoulder, so he's with me.

01:59:10.364 --> 01:59:17.254
MATT: Okay. As Frumpkin appears on the shoulder,
one of the watch goes, "Oh, where'd you come from,

01:59:17.254 --> 01:59:21.934
"little one? Didn't even see you come in." Begins
scritching Frumpkin.

01:59:21.934 --> 01:59:25.297
LIAM: He's friendly. That's my pet cat.

01:59:25.297 --> 01:59:28.987
MATT: Doesn't even talk to you. Just looks at
Frumpkin. "Who's a cute little kitty? We don't get

01:59:28.987 --> 01:59:32.977
"cats much on this island. It's good to see one.
Wonder what ship you came aboard?"

01:59:32.977 --> 01:59:36.760
(laughter)

01:59:36.760 --> 01:59:38.991
LIAM: I'm thinking really bad thoughts.

01:59:41.720 --> 01:59:48.936
MATT: Eventually, as the crowd begins to part, you
see a number of the guard, a few of the bodyguards

01:59:48.936 --> 01:59:53.533
that you had seen previously sitting amongst the
shadows of the Throne Roost when you first arrived

01:59:53.533 --> 02:00:01.676
the night before. You guys came roaring into this
town; you definitely did. There you see Beauregard

02:00:01.676 --> 02:00:09.133
being flanked by three guards, one better-armored
than the others, and then there, stepping behind

02:00:09.133 --> 02:00:21.061
that, the looming figure of the Plank King. He
approaches. "So not here but 24 hours and you've

02:00:21.061 --> 02:00:29.307
"already made a mess of our little home, have you?
I could see the flames from my Roost. My crow's

02:00:29.307 --> 02:00:35.928
"men tell me they spotted you walking aboard the
Squalleater and assault Avantika, one of our own.

02:00:35.928 --> 02:00:44.770
"Apparently a few of you fleeing into the city. You
know I have my misgivings about trusting anyone,

02:00:44.770 --> 02:00:50.773
"but I'm far more likely to toss in with those that
I've mistrusted long enough to at least know where

02:00:50.773 --> 02:01:01.785
"they stand. I don't know a fucking bit about all
of you. So my other friend--" and he points

02:01:01.785 --> 02:01:09.570
towards Jamedi, who's now in the back, and the
rest of you see, "-- says that you've all come in

02:01:09.729 --> 02:01:16.233
"with her lot naught but maybe two weeks back, and
that not most of you have much of an experience on

02:01:16.233 --> 02:01:26.079
"the sea, naught but one. The rest of you still
haven't quite found your legs on the waters. I'm

02:01:26.079 --> 02:01:35.949
"going to ask you right now, what brought you out
there, to mucking with the pirates' deals? Speak up!"

02:01:36.846 --> 02:01:44.717
TRAVIS: We understand your distrust. We are new
here, and we only beg your patience as we prove

02:01:44.717 --> 02:01:54.328
ourselves before you. Avantika and her crew were
up to foul deeds. Our friend Beau here, I trust,

02:01:54.328 --> 02:02:00.252
has shown you her journal.

02:02:01.339 --> 02:02:06.346
MATT: He reaches back in his pocket and goes, "Oh,
right. Here," and gives it to Solon, who goes,

02:02:06.346 --> 02:02:13.049
"Oh, all right. This is not a language I really
know--"

02:02:13.049 --> 02:02:14.589
MARISHA: There's a cipher in the front.

02:02:14.589 --> 02:02:15.400
MATT: "Oh, yeah."

02:02:15.400 --> 02:02:16.953
LIAM: Yeah, it's wedged into the back page.

02:02:16.953 --> 02:02:20.780
MATT: He takes it and pulls it out, looks at it.
"Oh, fuck me, this is--"

02:02:20.780 --> 02:02:23.231
MARISHA: Yeah, it's pretty good work, right?

02:02:24.184 --> 02:02:29.737
MATT: "Sir, with all due respect, it's going to
take me a long while to do this. This is elaborate."

02:02:29.737 --> 02:02:32.746
MARISHA: I told you, yeah.

02:02:33.086 --> 02:02:37.691
TALIESIN: I think there's already some work that
can be checked, if that speeds it up. I mean, that

02:02:37.691 --> 02:02:38.839
should be--

02:02:38.839 --> 02:02:40.155
MATT: The Plank King goes, "Shh."

02:02:40.155 --> 02:02:42.658
TALIESIN: Oh, yeah.

02:02:42.658 --> 02:02:48.595
MATT: "You said there's some special parts here,
of looking to overturn me or something? What pages

02:02:48.655 --> 02:02:50.524
"are that at?"

02:02:50.524 --> 02:02:55.928
LIAM: Excuse me, I am the one who deciphered this.
That is near the end.

02:02:55.928 --> 02:02:57.984
MARISHA: He's our Solon.

02:02:58.346 --> 02:03:03.298
MATT: Solon goes, "Oh! I'd very much like to have
a conversation with you."

02:03:03.298 --> 02:03:08.935
LIAM: As you will, if that is welcome here, but
yeah. The bit about her being a traitor to the

02:03:08.935 --> 02:03:16.572
Plank King, and wanting to rule over the entire
sea, and have the Plank King-- I believe the words

02:03:16.572 --> 02:03:24.144
are, if I remember correctly, because my memory is
spotty, "bend the knee."

02:03:24.144 --> 02:03:25.762
MATT: You point out the space where that was.

02:03:25.762 --> 02:03:27.520
LIAM: Is near the end, ja, right here.

02:03:27.520 --> 02:03:28.961
MATT: Thumbs through, and he goes--

02:03:28.961 --> 02:03:29.715
LIAM: It's complex.

02:03:29.715 --> 02:03:38.357
MATT: "Okay. O great king, give me a bit of time
with this, if you don't mind?" He looks around.

02:03:38.357 --> 02:03:43.990
Everyone's looking at him. At this moment he
glances around and sees the dozens and dozens of

02:03:43.990 --> 02:03:47.220
eyes locked on him, and he starts getting a little
nervous. You see a little sweat drop on his

02:03:47.220 --> 02:03:51.591
forehead, and he adjusts his glasses again.
They're starting to fog a bit. He goes, (clears

02:03:51.591 --> 02:03:55.728
throat), plops down, and starts going through, and
pulls out paper and a quill. He sets up in the

02:03:55.728 --> 02:04:00.375
middle of the dock area and starts going through
and point-by-point deciphering and translating

02:04:00.375 --> 02:04:04.043
each part of the cipher over to one of his empty
pages.

02:04:04.043 --> 02:04:07.136
TRAVIS: Great king, if we may, time we have.

02:04:07.136 --> 02:04:09.085
MATT: "That we do."

02:04:09.085 --> 02:04:16.377
TRAVIS: It's at your whim that we serve. I think
it would be only fair to ask that we remain under

02:04:16.377 --> 02:04:20.754
guard while your compatriot here translates that
text.

02:04:20.754 --> 02:04:22.556
MATT: "Oh, we're standing right here."

02:04:22.556 --> 02:04:24.377
TRAVIS: Fair enough.

02:04:24.377 --> 02:04:30.466
MATT: "You still haven't answered my question.
What brought you to these waters? Why'd you throw

02:04:30.466 --> 02:04:34.624
"in with her lot?" You see now, they're bringing
Avantika forward with the rest of you.

02:04:34.624 --> 02:04:44.213
MARISHA: Well, we're from Wildemount. Hired
mercenaries from the Empire. I'm with a secret

02:04:44.213 --> 02:04:57.977
order of the monks from the Cobalt Soul, known as
the Expositors. Avantika has been a person of

02:04:57.977 --> 02:05:04.288
interest that we've been wanting to investigate
for some time, and I was sent to do that. So,

02:05:04.288 --> 02:05:11.754
unfortunately, our business has nothing to do with
you fine folk here of Darktow. It only has to deal

02:05:11.754 --> 02:05:19.788
with Avantika. She's disrupted our shores enough.
We decided to investigate.

02:05:19.788 --> 02:05:22.967
MATT: "Where does your allegiance lie?"

02:05:22.967 --> 02:05:32.210
MARISHA: My allegiance is completely separate and
isolated from any persons here. My allegiance is

02:05:32.210 --> 02:05:35.726
with the Cobalt Soul.

02:05:35.726 --> 02:05:43.722
MATT: His eyes narrow. Make a deception check.
I'll say with advantage because you did drop the

02:05:43.722 --> 02:05:50.262
Cobalt Soul. In particular with the Plank King,
that has meaning.

02:05:50.262 --> 02:05:52.328
LIAM: I would like to read her as well.

02:05:52.328 --> 02:05:54.482
MATT: Insight check.

02:05:54.482 --> 02:05:55.965
LIAM: At disadvantage.

02:05:55.965 --> 02:05:57.491
MATT: Yes, for you.

02:05:57.491 --> 02:06:00.864
MARISHA: 22.

02:06:00.864 --> 02:06:05.135
MATT: The Plank King nods and goes--

02:06:05.135 --> 02:06:07.359
MARISHA: My voice is shaking. I'm so nervous.

02:06:07.359 --> 02:06:08.873
LIAM: 22 for me.

02:06:08.873 --> 02:06:17.577
MATT: Yeah, you barely see through. There's a hint
of truth, and there's a hint of not so true. It's

02:06:17.577 --> 02:06:19.137
a half-truth.

02:06:19.137 --> 02:06:22.535
LIAM: Caleb sees it! Go away, Fjord! Go away!

02:06:22.535 --> 02:06:25.921
MARISHA: Mixed lies or half-truths.

02:06:25.921 --> 02:06:31.215
MATT: The Plank King nods and goes, "Ah, the
Archives. I've had some dealings."

02:06:31.215 --> 02:06:34.924
MARISHA: Hmm. So you have your library card?

02:06:34.924 --> 02:06:47.605
MATT: "Not much of a reader. But your folk have
done good work for our interests in the past. So!

02:06:47.605 --> 02:06:54.281
"It's the woman of the hour. What have you to say
about yourself when these strangers have come

02:06:54.281 --> 02:06:59.118
"waltzing into our little haven and causing all
sorts of ruckus. Murdering your crew and making

02:06:59.118 --> 02:07:10.599
"these claims against you. Known you for years."
Avantika, hand behind in shackles goes, "Well."

02:07:10.599 --> 02:07:19.003
Her face, you can see bits where dirt, sweat lines
have made their way across and down the sides of

02:07:19.003 --> 02:07:25.589
her chin and jaw. Looking intently at the rest of
you with a forced smile through her teeth, there

02:07:25.596 --> 02:07:33.370
is a look of murderous rage and loss in her eyes,
as you have murdered a majority of her crew. She

02:07:33.425 --> 02:07:44.569
goes, "Well, I can guarantee that I kept no
journal. They came to me at sea with discussion of

02:07:44.569 --> 02:07:53.671
"perhaps coming and joining my crew, looking for
means of aid and gold. They began to talk of this

02:07:53.671 --> 02:08:06.710
"strange entity, this Uk'otoa. Well, I followed
suit. I wanted to make for some kind of alliance.

02:08:06.710 --> 02:08:13.441
"I found particular interest with one of their
individuals." She looks over towards Fjord, "But

02:08:13.441 --> 02:08:20.206
"it seems such a romance was merely just another
way to try and toss me to the proverbial wolves,

02:08:20.206 --> 02:08:28.895
"or merrow if it will. They've now killed my crew.
They've taken a number of my things, damaged my

02:08:28.895 --> 02:08:37.425
"ship, and they're trying to smear my name. One who
has walked alongside you and all of you fine, fine

02:08:37.425 --> 02:08:44.847
"folks for the past ten years! Even using the
memory of Vandren against me." You hear a few

02:08:44.847 --> 02:08:55.083
voices go like, (murmuring) "Vandren." "Vandren
raised this one and he sabotaged his ship. Blew it

02:08:55.083 --> 02:09:01.583
"asunder in the middle of the ocean. That was the
last he was seen. He's already killed one of our

02:09:01.583 --> 02:09:05.797
"own. Is this untrue?"

02:09:05.797 --> 02:09:08.138
TRAVIS: (stuttering) Is she talking to me?

02:09:08.138 --> 02:09:08.834
MATT: Yeah.

02:09:08.834 --> 02:09:13.986
LAURA: From the crowd, I'm going to go: She's
lying! We always knew she had it in for the Plank King!

02:09:13.986 --> 02:09:18.250
MATT: Someone goes, "Shh!" All eyes are on you.

02:09:18.250 --> 02:09:23.295
TRAVIS: Plank King, if I may. My ears, though
pointy, can only stand a certain amount of

02:09:23.295 --> 02:09:29.781
dishonesty. I would prefer to cut through the
bull. There are those of us among us who can make

02:09:29.781 --> 02:09:38.119
sure that the truth is spoken here. I would beg of
you to allow that to happen now.

02:09:38.119 --> 02:09:40.764
MATT: Make a persuasion check.

02:09:44.524 --> 02:09:45.954
TRAVIS: Natural 20.

02:09:45.954 --> 02:09:55.616
(cheering)

02:09:55.616 --> 02:10:02.272
MATT: The Plank King gives you this very severe
look. His eyes narrowed and glancing you up and

02:10:02.345 --> 02:10:10.689
down, almost piercing you with but a glance. He
raises his hand with a grin and goes, "Oh. What's

02:10:10.689 --> 02:10:12.972
"necessary for such a thing?"

02:10:12.972 --> 02:10:14.964
TRAVIS: (whispering) Who has that shit?

02:10:14.964 --> 02:10:17.692
MARISHA: I do and Jester does.

02:10:17.692 --> 02:10:19.208
TRAVIS: You do?

02:10:19.208 --> 02:10:24.361
MARISHA: Yeah. It takes me literally punching the
shit out of Avantika though.

02:10:25.694 --> 02:10:33.655
TRAVIS: Honorable Plank King, the means justify
the ends. My compatriot here will place her Cobalt

02:10:33.655 --> 02:10:38.716
knuckles upon the chin of Avantika and you will
hear the truth. You need but only ask your

02:10:38.716 --> 02:10:41.606
questions again.

02:10:41.606 --> 02:10:48.444
MATT: "Be my guest." Avantika is like, "What
is--"

02:10:48.444 --> 02:10:49.921
MARISHA: Before she-- (double punch)

02:10:49.921 --> 02:10:53.115
(laughter)

02:10:53.115 --> 02:10:57.215
MATT: She's manacled and being held by two guards
from behind. It's auto-hit.

02:10:57.215 --> 02:10:58.284
LIAM: Holy shit.

02:10:58.284 --> 02:10:59.907
MARISHA: Go for the temple.

02:10:59.907 --> 02:11:01.355
MATT: Do you have a ki point left?

02:11:01.355 --> 02:11:06.825
MARISHA: Yeah, I have all of my ki points left.
More or less. All but one. Yep.

02:11:06.825 --> 02:11:10.377
MATT: All right. What's the DC on that?

02:11:10.377 --> 02:11:17.231
MARISHA: Mine, I'm assuming, which is 14. Hang on.
Features and traits.

02:11:17.231 --> 02:11:19.764
MATT: Yeah, whatever your DC is for all of your
monk stuff.

02:11:19.764 --> 02:11:22.581
LIAM, SAM, and TRAVIS: (whispering) Monk stuff!

02:11:22.581 --> 02:11:23.948
MARISHA: Yeah, 14.

02:11:23.948 --> 02:11:38.865
MATT: Okay. It's a wisdom save. No. That's a
natural eight plus four. 12. So all these

02:11:38.865 --> 02:11:43.466
different hits and pressure points are hit, like
under the chin, that area. Another to the sternum

02:11:43.466 --> 02:11:48.928
and another that clocks the temple. And Avantika
just, "Ugh!" (heavy breathing)

02:11:48.928 --> 02:11:55.615
MARISHA: They are unable to speak a deliberate lie
for one minute and all charisma checks have advantage.

02:11:55.615 --> 02:11:59.144
MATT: Intimidation checks? Oh, charisma checks!
Yeah, persuasion, everything else. That's right, yeah.

02:11:59.144 --> 02:12:02.062
LIAM: Mein Gott.

02:12:02.062 --> 02:12:06.291
TRAVIS: Make sure you tell the Plank King it's a
limited time engagement.

02:12:06.291 --> 02:12:07.673
MATT: She's like: "Ugh!"

02:12:07.673 --> 02:12:12.486
MARISHA: You have 60 seconds, but I have more
knuckles.

02:12:12.486 --> 02:12:22.406
MATT: The Plank King steps forward. "Avantika, is
what they're saying true?" She goes, (frustrated

02:12:22.406 --> 02:12:34.797
grunt) Glances aside. Doesn't respond. He leans
forward closer. "Tell me."

02:12:34.797 --> 02:12:37.980
LIAM: (whispering) Silence speaks volumes,
though.

02:12:37.980 --> 02:12:44.584
MATT: "Is what they're saying true? Is that book
containing passages where you're looking to take

02:12:44.584 --> 02:12:55.499
"this island for yourself?" Her eyes look away. She
just looks down at the rest of the dock. He leans

02:12:55.499 --> 02:13:01.364
in real close, pushing his forehead almost to
hers. "Look me in the eye, woman."

02:13:01.364 --> 02:13:04.499
MARISHA: Oh my god!

02:13:09.320 --> 02:13:28.528
MATT: She just doesn't meet his gaze. "Hmm. By the
power of The Revelry that surrounds me, let this

02:13:28.528 --> 02:13:40.694
"be a lesson to those who would work against the
words we swore to each other on this land. May

02:13:40.694 --> 02:13:49.940
"your memory be besmirched for the few days it's
recalled." He reaches forward and grabs Avantika

02:13:49.940 --> 02:13:54.108
by the throat and lifts her up and she's fighting
against it. He lifts her and looks at her. "I hope

02:13:54.108 --> 02:14:01.027
"your sea god, whatever it is, is very merciful on
the other side." (cracking) He breaks her neck

02:14:01.027 --> 02:14:10.676
with one hand. Her body goes limp in his grasp and
he throws it to the docks. "Don't worry about the

02:14:10.676 --> 02:14:20.020
"cipher." Solon goes, "It's actually quite
interesting. I'd like to continue." "Fine."

02:14:20.020 --> 02:14:23.226
LIAM: I worked through the night on that. It's
very interesting.

02:14:23.226 --> 02:14:27.632
MATT: "And it's really well done! I'm honestly
very taken aback by it. Your penmanship is quite

02:14:27.632 --> 02:14:28.711
"good as well."

02:14:28.711 --> 02:14:29.355
LIAM: Breakfast.

02:14:29.355 --> 02:14:32.139
SAM: I have a sample of her penmanship here if you
want to see some more of it.

02:14:32.139 --> 02:14:38.956
MATT: "Oh, certainly!" He goes and starts taking
it. At this point, the Plank King goes, "Take her

02:14:38.956 --> 02:14:51.672
"up top. She'll be the next on the pike. As for the
rest of you, you've pulled out a conspiracy, I'll

02:14:51.672 --> 02:14:58.158
"give you that. You've also snuck your way into The
Revelry under false pretenses. You've broken our

02:14:58.158 --> 02:15:10.823
"laws within but a day of being presented with
them, in multiple ways. That's a serious offense.

02:15:10.823 --> 02:15:27.805
"So hear my judgment upon these folk. You are
hereby banished from Darktow. Take the remnants of

02:15:27.805 --> 02:15:35.811
"the Squalleater as your own. Take whatever--" He
looks over towards the rest of the crew you hired,

02:15:35.811 --> 02:15:37.875
who are like (panicked panting).

02:15:37.875 --> 02:15:40.040
TRAVIS: (laughter) Those poor fuckers!

02:15:40.040 --> 02:15:45.884
MATT: They have had a terrible few weeks here!
Except for Orly, who's sitting there, smoking a

02:15:45.884 --> 02:15:49.966
pipe, and his one eye goes.

02:15:49.966 --> 02:15:51.323
TRAVIS: Stone-cold killer.

02:15:51.323 --> 02:15:53.283
LIAM: He is so stoned.

02:15:53.283 --> 02:16:03.060
MATT: "Take the ship you've thereby damaged. Limp
your way beyond the reefs. We're going to burn the

02:16:03.060 --> 02:16:10.705
"colors of that ship. Should you ever return to the
outskirts of the Dragshallow, we won't hesitate

02:16:10.705 --> 02:16:15.031
"but sink you to the depths below."

02:16:15.031 --> 02:16:19.694
TRAVIS: That is beyond a generous sentence.

02:16:19.694 --> 02:16:26.941
MATT: "Unshackle them. This stands immediately. I
hope you have enough supplies in that boat to last

02:16:26.941 --> 02:16:28.824
"you the rest of the journey."

02:16:28.824 --> 02:16:30.300
SAM: (whispering) I don't think that we do.

02:16:30.300 --> 02:16:31.829
TALIESIN: We'll be fine.

02:16:31.829 --> 02:16:35.685
TRAVIS: We'll make do. We will leave with great
haste.

02:16:35.685 --> 02:16:43.527
MATT: "Good. Tell the Archives that the Plank King
sends his regards."

02:16:43.527 --> 02:16:47.500
MARISHA: Will do, good sir.

02:16:47.500 --> 02:16:49.715
MATT: "Now fucking go!"

